I am not sure why you are writing vanilla JavaScript when you have an option of using jQuery. 

Nevertheless, your function check() has many mistakes in it. Primarily being that the input variable is being re-written every time getElementsByTagName is called. I am guessing what you are trying to do is to get all the input, select and radio elements and check whether or not they have values, and accordingly update your filled variable.

getElementsByTagName returns an array of elements.
You can use the ES6 spread operator and forEach to check for inputs that have values.

